ketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 549, \"end\": 555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manila\", \"score\": 0.9995986184615447, \"rank\": 0.00040153935789703993, \"text\": \"Manila\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manila\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manila\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The oldest in the team at 39, James proved he remains the top dog by delivering 25 points, 7 assists, and 6 rebounds as the Americans avoided a stunning loss to the South Sudanese, who are ranked 33rd in the world.\", \"from\": 564, \"to\": 778, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 594, \"end\": 599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.002002882151778e-20, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}, {\"begin\": 729, \"end\": 743, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Sudan\", \"score\": 0.9999967186358112, \"rank\": 3.2813738193258244e-06, \"text\": \"South Sudanese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Sudan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Sudan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"South Sudan took a 100-99 lead off a booming JT Thor three-pointer with 20 seconds remaining.\", \"from\": 780, \"to\": 873, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 825, \"end\": 832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JT_Thor\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"JT Thor\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JT_Thor\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JT_Thor\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But James countered with a layup 12 seconds later to give Team USA the upper hand.\", \"from\": 874, \"to\": 956, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 878, \"end\": 883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.002002882151778e-20, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}, {\"begin\": 932, \"end\": 940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.8113148878210866e-13, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Carlik Jones managed to shake off Jrue Holiday for a clear shot at the game-winner, but his runner off the glass misfired, while Wenyen Gabriel missed his putback as South Sudan fell short after frittering away a 16-point lead.\", \"from\": 958, \"to\": 1185, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 958, \"end\": 970, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlik_Jones\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlik Jones\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlik_Jones\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlik_Jones\"}, {\"begin\": 1087, \"end\": 1101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wenyen_Gabriel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wenyen Gabriel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wenyen_Gabriel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wenyen_Gabriel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Anthony Davis backstopped James with 15 points, 11 rebounds, and 2 blocks; Joel Embiid finished with 14 points and 7 rebounds; while Anthony Edwards and Stephen Curry supplied 11 and 10 points, respectively.\", \"from\": 1187, \"to\": 1394, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1187, \"end\": 1